Sheryl Swoopes scored 24 points as the Houston
Comets rallied to beat the Seattle Storm 67-59 Tuesday night for
their 10th consecutive victory.
article.headline: Swoopes scores 24 as Comets rally from 18 down

images.name: Barnes_Adia 020709 inline
images.caption: Seattle's Adia Barnes pulls a rebound from Houston's Michelle Snow, but the Comets grabbed the victory away from the Storm.

article.linkText: Swoopes leads Comets to big comeback
article.story:
HOUSTON (AP) -- Sheryl Swoopes scored 24 points as the Houston
Comets rallied to beat the Seattle Storm 67-59 Tuesday night for
their 10th consecutive victory.

<photo1>

	   Houston (15-3) hasn't lost since June 13 at Washington, and is
8-0 at home since an opening day defeat against defending WNBA champion
Los Angeles.

	   Lauren Jackson scored 16 points for Seattle (8-10).

	   ''In the first half, we weren't aggressive enough on defense and
dug ourselves into a hole,'' Swoopes said. ''At halftime, coach told
us that we could play better and we know no team can run with us.''

	   Swoopes made 10 of her 19 shots and grabbed five rebounds. Tina
Thompson scored 18 points and had 13 rebounds for the Comets, who
trailed by 18 points in the first half.

	   ''In the first half, we just let them run,'' Houston coach Van
Chancellor said. ''Anything they wanted to do, anywhere they wanted
to shoot, we let them have it. In the second half, we didn't let
them run their offense.''

	   Seattle led 38-20 with 4:37 left in the first half, but Houston
scored six of the next eight points and 12 of the first 13 after
halftime.

	   ''The last thing I told the team at the end of halftime was that
we did not see the real Houston Comets in the first half,'' Seattle
coach Lin Dunn said.

	   ''I feel good about the fact that we played with them after they
battled back, but we missed a few opportunities late and that cost
us.''
